sentence: John Wayne Conlee (born August 11, 1946) is an American country music singer.
John Wayne Conlee (born August 11, 1946) is an American country music singer.
Conlee was born on a tobacco farm in Versailles, Kentucky.
By age 10, Conlee had begun singing and playing guitar, and later sang tenor in a barbershop quartet.
Conlee did not immediately take up a musical career, instead becoming a licensed mortician, employed by Duell-Clark Funeral Chapel, and later a disc jockey at radio station WLAC.
By 1971, he moved to Nashville, Tennessee, in pursuit of a musical career, signing to ABC Records in 1976.
